		<p><b><b>A lot of your doll clothing is vintage. Is there a specific era of fashion that you favor over others? Do you have any favorite online shops that you buy clothing from? <b></b></b></b></p>
		<p>I love mod era clothing. 1970 was a great year for my dollies. Vintage Skipper doll clothing is my absolute obsession - it fits Blythe dolls so well. I buy it from other collectors and from eBay mostly. I’m a total bargain hound and I am always stalking a good vintage deal. I do that in real life too, I barely ever buy anything new. Makers of retro styled clothing that I also like are <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/endangeredsissy"><b>Endangered Sissy</b></a> and <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/PlasticFashion"><b>Plastic Fashion</b></a> on Etsy and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/vintagecity_gem/"><b>Vintage City Gem</b></a> on Instagram. For street style, my absolute FAV is <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/Pomipomari"><b>Pomipomari</b></a> Pomipomari on etsy (she’s on <a href="https://www.instagram.com/Pomipomari"><b>IG</b></a> too)</b></p><br>
		<br>
	</div>
	<div class="img">
