			<%= image_tag 'sparklecious4.png'%>
		</center><br>
		<p><b>Do you have any tips for the beginning doll photographer?</b></p>
		<p>Work to your strengths and chase the light. I have no technical skill as a photographer and I just use my phone, so I decided to concentrate on composition and colour, and realised early on that if the light is bad, the image is bad. I built a DIY lightbox off an online tutorial and that made ALL the difference to my image quality. There are lots of blog posts about framing, composition etc, I’d read those.&nbsp;Oh, and it takes practice to pose your dollies - mine all looked…differently abled…for many months until I got better at it. I’m still pretty lazy about that, but I know that about myself and I play to my strengths!&nbsp;</p><br>
		<br>
